   - VSS to GND
   - VDD to 5V

   - D4 to digital pin 5 on Arduino

   - D6 to digital pin 3 on Arduino

   - VCC to 5V
   - GND to GND
   - DQ to digital pin 7 on Arduino (with a 4.7K Ohm pull-up resistor between VCC and DQ)

   **Or Temperature Sensor (LM35):**
   - VCC to 5V
   - GND to GND

First, ensure you have the necessary packages installed. You will need the `apache-airflow-providers-microsoft-azure` package for Azure integration and `authlib` for OAuth2 support.

```bash
pip install apache-airflow-providers-microsoft-azure authlib
```

### Step 2: Register an Application in Azure AD

1. Go to the Azure portal and navigate to "Azure Active Directory".
2. Select "App registrations" and click on "New registration".
3. Fill in the necessary details and register the application.
4. Note down the Application (client) ID and Directory (tenant) ID.
5. Create a client secret for the application and note it down.
6. Configure the redirect URI to point to your Airflow web server's callback URL (e.g., `http://your-airflow-webserver/oauth-authorized/azure`).

### Step 3: Configure Airflow Web Server

Update your `airflow.cfg` file to include the necessary OAuth2 configuration. You can add the following section to your `airflow.cfg`:

The first time I saw the word “derivative” was in a review of a movie I was dying to see. The reviewer said the movie was “derivative” and I thought, “Oh, that sounds good.” I was in my early teens and I thought the word meant something like “riveting.” I thought it meant the movie was so good that it was the source from which other movies flowed.

I was wrong.

“Derivative” means “unoriginal.” It means the movie is a copy of other movies. It means the movie is a pale imitation of other movies. It means the movie is a rip-off of other movies.

I was disappointed.

But I still wanted to see the movie.

I saw the movie and I liked it. I thought it was original and fresh. I thought it was riveting. I thought it was the source from which other movies flowed.

I was wrong.

The movie was derivative. It was a copy of other movies. It was a pale imitation of other movies. It was a rip-off of other movies.

But I still liked it.
